{"title_page": "List of Healin' Good PreCure episodes", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Healin' Good PreCure'' episodes}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| italic_title = no\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| starring         =\n| country          = Japan\n| network          = [[All-Nippon News Network|ANN]] ([[Asahi Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]], [[TV Asahi]])\n| first_aired      = February 2, 2020 \n| last_aired       = Present\n| num_episodes     = <!--- 49 --->\n| prev_series      = [[List of Star Twinkle PreCure episodes|Star Twinkle Precure]]\n| next_series      = \n| episode_list     =\n}}\n''[[Healin' Good PreCure]]'' is the seventeenth television [[anime]] series in [[Izumi Todo]]'s ''[[Pretty Cure]]'' franchise, produced by [[Asahi Broadcasting Corporation]] and animated by [[Toei Animation]]. The series aired in Japan from February 2, 2020, succeeding ''[[Star Twinkle PreCure]]'' in its initial time slot. The opening theme is \"Healin' Good Pretty Cure Touch!!\" (\u30d2\u30fc\u30ea\u30f3\u30b0\u3063\u3069\u2665\u30d7\u30ea\u30ad\u30e5\u30a2 Touch!!) by Rie Kitagawa, while the first ending theme is \"Miracle and a Link Ring!\" (\u30df\u30e9\u30af\u30eb\u3063\u3068 Link Ring\uff01) by [[Machico (singer)|Machico]].<ref>https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-25/healin-good-precure-tv-anime-unveils-cast-staff-story-february-2-debut/.154757</ref> \n\n__TOC__\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episode list==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #ed7cae;\"\n! style=\"width:1%;\"  | {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title\n! style=\"width:14%;\" | Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = Holding Hands Tightly! We're Pretty Cure\u2665Cure Grace\n| TranslitTitle       = Te to Te de Kyun! Futari de Purikyua\u2665Kyua Gur\u0113su\n| NativeTitle         = \u624b\u3068\u624b\u3067\u30ad\u30e5\u30f3\uff01\u4e8c\u4eba\u3067\u30d7\u30ea\u30ad\u30e5\u30a2\u2665\u30ad\u30e5\u30a2\u30b0\u30ec\u30fc\u30b9\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|2|2}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka Hanadera is a second year middle school student who has just moved to Sukoyaka City, famous for being a healthy city. Nodoka suffered from a respiratory condition so her parents decided to move to help her recovery. Nodoka takes in her new surroundings, eager to help out and meet new people. While relaxing in the park, Nodoka suddenly witnesses a monster attack and upon hearing of a dog in trouble, goes off to find it. Nodoka finds the dog along with three Healing Animals: Rabirin, Pegitan and Nyatoran. The Animals explain that the dog is named Princess Latte and that they all come from the Healing Garden, a place in the center of the Earth that helps keep the planet healthy. However the garden is under a threat from the Bj\u00f6gens, who wants to infect the world with disease. The Bj\u00f6gen General Daruizen created the monster, known as a MegaBj\u00f6gen, by infecting an elemental spirit. The Animals were asked by Latte's mother, Queen Tiatine, to find those destined to be their partners and become the Legendary Precure and fight the Bj\u00f6gens. Latte is sensitive to the monster attacks and becomes sick when one appears. However, Nodoka's feelings of wanting to help resonate with Rabirin and allow her to transform into Cure Grace. Cure Grace then defeats the MegaBj\u00f6gen and purifies the Flower spirit, making Latte healthy again.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| Title               = No Longer Partners!? I Guess I'm No Good?\n| TranslitTitle       = P\u0101ton\u0101 Kaish\u014d!? Watashi ja Dame Nano?\n| NativeTitle         = \u30d1\u30fc\u30c8\u30ca\u30fc\u89e3\u6d88\uff01\uff1f\u308f\u305f\u3057\u3058\u3083\u30c0\u30e1\u306a\u306e\uff1f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|2|9}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka takes Latte home and asks her parents if she can keep her, to which they agree. Nodoka sneaks the animals into her room where they tell her all about Latte, the Healing Garden and the Bj\u00f6gens. The next day Nodoka goes to her first day at school, the Animals come with her in the hope of finding partners for Pegitan and Nyatoran. Nodoka discovers she is in the same class as Chiyu Sawaizumi and Hinata Hiramitsu, two girls she met the previous day. After school, Nodoka is asked if she wants to join one of the sports clubs. While enthusiastic about it, Nodoka soon reveals she is poorly unskilled at everything, much to Rabirin's dismay. Thinking Nodoka is unfit to be a Precure, Rabirin breaks off their partnership and runs off, with Pegitan pursuing her. Nodoka returns home hoping to find Rabirin, but when Latte falls ill, she returns to school to find Daruizen has created another MegaBj\u00f6gen. Nodoka attempts to fight the MegaBj\u00f6gen on her own but is easily overpowered. Latte calls out and draws Rabirin and Pegitan back to her. Rabirin asks why Nodoka is so determined, at which she reveals to Rabirin about her illness when she was younger, and that renders her unable to participate in sports. Hoping to make up for her lost time, Nodoka wants to help protect the world as a Precure. Rabirin realizes she was wrong about Nodoka and apologizes; the two reconcile. Nodoka transforms into Cure Grace and defeats the MegaBj\u00f6gen, restoring the Tree spirit and Latte.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| Title               = Overflowing Feelings! Transform Into Cure Fontaine!\n| TranslitTitle       = Wakiagaru Omoi! Henshin! Kyua Font\u0113nu!\n| NativeTitle         = \u6e67\u304d\u4e0a\u304c\u308b\u60f3\u3044\uff01\u5909\u8eab\uff01\u30ad\u30e5\u30a2\u30d5\u30a9\u30f3\u30c6\u30fc\u30cc\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|2|16}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka overhears her classmates taking about the recent monster attacks, but Rabirin implores her to keep her Precure identity a secret. However Chiyu asks Nodoka about the attack the previous day, not revealing she saw Nodoka with Latte and the Healing Animals at school, but Nodoka manages to evade her questions. Meanwhile, Nyatoran leaves Pegitan to look after Latte while he tries to find a partner, but Latte sneaks off leaving Pegitan to find her. Latte manages to reach the school where she is found by Chiyu, who returns her to Nodoka. Chiyu once again tries to question Nodoka about her involvement with the monster attacks but Nodoka again evades her. Chiyu decides to drop the interrogation and invites Nodoka to her home. Chiyu's family own an inn with a hot spring and she allows Nodoka to use it freely. However another Bj\u00f6gen General, Shindoine, infects the water source to create a MegaBj\u00f6gen. Chiyu goes to investigate and witnesses Nodoka transforming into Cure Grace. Cure Grace battles the MegaBj\u00f6gen but is injured protecting Chiyu. Chiyu then spots Pegitan and asks him if she can use his power to help Nodoka, revealing she overhead him saying he felt useless despite wanting to help when he was in the hot spring earlier. Chiyu's feelings resonate with Pegitan and she transforms into Cure Fontaine. With Cure Grace's help, Cure Fontaine defeats the MegaBj\u00f6gen and purifies the Water spirit, before healing Latte. Afterwards Nodoka explains to Chiyu all about the MegaBj\u00f6gen and Chiyu asks to look after Pegitan.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| Title               = I Want To Be Cute! The Birth of Cure Sparkle\n| TranslitTitle       = Kawa\u012b! Naritai! Kyua Sup\u0101kuru Tanj\u014d\n| NativeTitle         = \u30ab\u30ef\u30a4\u30a4\uff01\u306a\u308a\u305f\u3044\uff01\u30ad\u30e5\u30a2\u30b9\u30d1\u30fc\u30af\u30eb\u8a95\u751f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|2|23}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka calls Chiyu over to her house when it appears that Latte has become ill. However as there doesn't appear to be a Bj\u00f6gen attack anywhere, Chiyu believes that Latte is just tired and thinks they should take her to the local Veterinary Hospital run by Hinata's family. Meanwhile Nyatoran continues to look for a partner when he spots Hinata, who drops her make-up before rushing off. Nyatoran retrieve the make-up and chases after Hinata to return it, but trips and is saved by her. Hinata expresses her gratiude for the return of her make-up, but her obsessive fawning over him causes Nyatoran to reveal he can talk. Nodoka and Chiyu take Latte to see Hinata's brother, who tells them Latte just needs rest. But when Hinata barges in claiming to have found a talking cat, the girls quickly stop her from revealing the truth. When it seems that Hinata is unlikely to forget about Nyatoran, he decides to pretend to be a random taking cat in order to convince Hinata to keep him a secret. Hinata suddenly realizes she is late for a shopping trip with her friends so all three girls go to the Mall. However another Bj\u00f6gen General, Guaiwaru, infects a mirror to create a MegaBj\u00f6gen which begins to destroy the Mall. Hinata gets separated from Nodoka and Chiyu, Nyatoran tries to get Hinata to leave but she is determined to find them. When Hinata locates the girls she witnesses them transform into Precure and start fighting the MegaBj\u00f6gen. Despite the danger Hinata becomes enamored by how cute they look, and when the MegaBj\u00f6gen captures the Cures she openly tries to defend them but is knocked aside. Nyatoran, impressed by Hinata's spirit offers to be her partner and allows her to transform into Cure Sparkle. Cure Sparkle defeats the MegaBj\u00f6gen, purifying the Light spirit and healing Latte. Afterwards Hinata apologizes to her friends for being late. \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| Title               = Awkward Day at the Aquarium! We're All So Different\n| TranslitTitle       = Kimazui Suizokukan! Chiguhagu na Watashitachi\n| NativeTitle         = \u6c17\u307e\u305a\u3044\u6c34\u65cf\u9928\uff01\u30c1\u30b0\u30cf\u30b0\u306a\u308f\u305f\u3057\u305f\u3061\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|3|1}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka and Chiyu keep reminding Hinata to keep their Precure identities a secret, as she nearly lets it slip whenever her friends talk about the monster attacks. Things begin to get more problematic when it appears that Chiyu and Hinata's personalities clash with each other. Chiyu is calm and collective while Hinata is head strong and excitable, both girls confide in Nodoka that they think they can't get along with each other. Nodoka expresses her concern to her mother, who gives Nodoka a set of tickets to the Aqaurium so the three girls can spent time together. At the Aquarium, Chiyu and Hinata start to get on well together but things take a turn when Pegitan goes missing and is mistaken for an escaped Penguin. To make matters worse, Shindoine creates a MegaBj\u00f6gen to terrorize the Aquarium. Since Chiyu can't transform without Pegitan, she and Hinata go to find him while Nodoka goes to deal with the MegaBj\u00f6gen. However Chiyu and Hinata find Shindoine, who has captured Pegitan, and the MegaBj\u00f6gen first. Chiyu tries to handle the situation calmly but Hinata barges in and attempts to rescue Pegitan by force. Nodoka arrives just as Shindoine releases Pegitan, and the three girls transform to battle the MegaBj\u00f6gen. Cure Fontaine purifies the Bubble spirit, but afterwards Chiyu reprimands Hinata for being reckless and putting herself in danger. Hinata apologizes and both girls reaffirm their friendship.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| Title               = Where's Mom ~latte? The Great Escape!\n| TranslitTitle       = Mama wa Doko ~rate? Orusuban Daidass\u014d!\n| NativeTitle         = \u30de\u30de\u306f\u3069\u3053\u30e9\u30c6\uff1f\u304a\u308b\u3059\u3070\u3093\u5927\u8131\u8d70\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|3|8}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka introduces her new friends to her parents, both of whom are relieved that their daughter is getting along so well. Since Nodoka appears to be able to look after herself better, her mother, Yasuko, thinks this is the right time for her to go back to work as a delivery driver, which Nodoka is thrilled to hear. Unfortunately it means that Latte will be stuck at home alone for a few hours a day as Nokoka and her father also have school and work respectively. Latte becomes downhearted at being alone, even when the Healing Animals come to keep her company. One day Latte manages to escape the house so Pegitan and Nyatoran chase after her while Rabirin fetches Nodoka and her friends. They find Latte at the delivery company and Nodoka realises Latte misses Yasuko. Latte tells Nodoka that Yasuko used to pet her and make her happy when she was at home, and that she reminded Latte of her own mother, Queen Teatinu. Suddenly Latte senses there is a MegaBj\u00f6gen present and the girls rush off to a strawberry farm, where Yasuko is currently picking up a shipment of strawberries. The MegaBj\u00f6gen infects the farm and Daruizen knocks Yasuko unconscious. Nodoka, Chiyu and Hinata transform and fight the MegaBj\u00f6gen, but Cure Grace is separated from the group and ends up trapped in the infection. Daruizen confronts Grace but she manages to break free of the infection and continues to battle the MegaBj\u00f6gen. The Cures manage to defeat the MegaBj\u00f6gen and Cure Grace purifies the Harvest spirit, who gives her a new elemental bottle.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| Title               = Big News!? Nodoka's Secret\n| TranslitTitle       = Dai Suk\u016bpu!? Nodoka no Himitsu\n| NativeTitle         = \u5927\u30b9\u30af\u30fc\u30d7!\uff1f\u306e\u3069\u304b\u306e\u79d8\u5bc6\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|3|15}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka gets the feeling she is being watched all the time, only to discover that the editor of the school newspaper, Michio Masuko, is spying on her. When confronted, Michio tells Nodoka's he thinks she is responsible for the monster attacks. He vows to discover the truth and follows Nodoka everywhere. One day while walking in the forest, Nodoka spots Michio and attempts to run away from him, only to trip and injure herself. Michio helps her before apologizing for scaring her. Nodoka returns home, but Michio wanders into the forest and discovers Guaiwaru summoning a MegaBj\u00f6gen. Michio confronts the MegaBj\u00f6gen but it knocks him over and he loses his glasses. The Cures arrive and fight the MegaBj\u00f6gen and purify the Rain spirit. Afterwards Nodoka helps Michio, who apologizes for suspecting her.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 8\n| Title               = Chiyu Can't Jump!? Trouble At The Athletics Tournament!\n| TranslitTitle       = Tobenai Chiyu!? Rikuj\u014d Taikai Dai Pinchi!\n| NativeTitle         = \u3068\u3079\u306a\u3044\u3061\u3086\uff01\uff1f\u9678\u4e0a\u5927\u4f1a\u5927\u30d4\u30f3\u30c1\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|3|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Chiyu is in training for an upcoming track and field event. However, she suddenly loses the ability to perform the high jump at her usual standards. Pegitan becomes worried and after consulting his treatment books, comes to the conclusion that Chiyu has a case of the 'Yips'. He confides in Nodoka and Hinata, who both reassure him and reveal that Chiyu has just lost some of her confidence, so they are making a banner to cheer her on. On the day of the event, Daruizen creates a MegaBj\u00f6gen to distrupt the activities. The Cures engage the MegaBj\u00f6gen and Cure Fontaine is able to use her jump abilities to find an opening in its ice shield and purify the Ice spirit. Afterwards the Ice spirit gives Chiyu a new elemental bottle, she also regains her confidence and manages to complete the high jump.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 9\n| Title               = Hinata's Cute Plan!\n| TranslitTitle       = Hinata no Kawa\u012b Daisakusen!\n| NativeTitle         = \u3072\u306a\u305f\u306e\u30ab\u30ef\u30a4\u30a4\u5927\u4f5c\u6226\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|3|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = Hinata notices that Nodoka has a photo collection but it does not contain any recent photos of her. Nodoka explains that she hasn't had her photo taken since before she was ill, causing Hinata to suddenly get an idea and drag Nodoka and Chiyu to the Mall. Hinata takes them to a shop which lets people borrow clothes and accessories to take pictures with. Hinata spends the day helping Nodoka and Chiyu make accessories, but Nodoka becomes overcome by the crowds and has to take a break. Hinata feels she pushed Nodoka too much but Nodoka reassures her she is fine. When Latte runs off, Hinata goes to retrieve her and discovers Shindione has created a MegaBj\u00f6gen to terrorise the Mall. Hinata decides to try and handle the monster herself but is easily overpowered before Nodoka and Chiyu come to her aid. After Hinata explains herself, Nodoka reassures her she has been very helpful to them and the three Cures engage the MegaBj\u00f6gen and defeat it with the help of Chiyu's new elemental bottle. After purifying the Gem spirit, Hinata takes Nodoka and Chiyu back to the shop to finish having their picture taken, which she presents to Nodoka to add to her photo collection.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 10\n| Title               = Emergency Treatment! There are lots of Megabj\u00f6gens!?\n| TranslitTitle       = Kinky\u016b Oteate! Megaby\u014dgen ga Ippai!?\n| NativeTitle         = \u7dca\u6025\u304a\u624b\u5f53\uff01\u30e1\u30ac\u30d3\u30e7\u30fc\u30b2\u30f3\u304c\u3044\u3063\u3071\u3044\uff01\uff1f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|5}}\n| ShortSummary        = Nodoka is excited to go on her first class trip with Chiyu and Hinata. The girls take a train ride to a museum where Nodoka meets a sculptor who makes art from glass. However, the girls are shocked to discover that the Healing Animals and Latte have decided to come and join them, despite being asked to stay home. Unfortunately, Guaiwaru summons a MegaBj\u00f6gen to infect the museum forcing the three to transform and fight it. To make matters worse, Cure Fontaine notices Latte becoming more sick and upon examining her, Latte reveals the presence of two additional MegaBj\u00f6gens. The Cures are forced to split up with Cure Grace opting to stay behind and protect the museum. However, the MegaBj\u00f6gens prove too powerful for each individual Cure to face alone so the three regroup at the museum to take care of Guaiwaru's MegaBj\u00f6gen before moving on to the next. Before leaving Cure Sparkle receives power from the purified Light Spirit.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 11\n| Title               = Combining Powers! Miracle Healing!\n| TranslitTitle       = Chikara o Hitotsu ni! Mirakuru H\u012bringu!\n| NativeTitle         = \u529b\u3092\u4e00\u3064\u306b\uff01\u30df\u30e9\u30af\u30eb\u30d2\u30fc\u30ea\u30f3\u30b0\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = The Cures race to the second MegaBj\u00f6gen, created by Shindione to pollute a river, managing to purify it before Cure Fontaine receives power from the Water spirit. The final MegaBj\u00f6gen created by Daruizen, is terrorizing a meadow of flowers and has become so strong the Cure are knocked away and lose their transformation when they attempt to fight it. Regrouping in the forest, the Cures wonder if they're too late to save the Flower spirit, but Nodoka rallies them and they transform again and engage the MegaBj\u00f6gen. Cure Grace encourages the Flower spirit to not give up and it manages to give her its power, which combines with the other spirit powers causing the Miracle Healing Bottle to appear. The Cures use the new bottle to perform Healing Oasis to defeat the MegaBj\u00f6gen and purify the Flower Spirit. However, unknown to the Cures a seed from the last MegaBj\u00f6gen goes unnoticed and infects a Nutria.\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 12\n| Title               = Thoughts As One! The Great Teamwork Plan\n| TranslitTitle       = Ishin Denshin! Ch\u012bmuw\u0101ku Daisakusen\n| NativeTitle         = \u4ee5\u5fc3\u4f1d\u5fc3\uff01\u3000\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u30ef\u30fc\u30af\u5927\u4f5c\u6226\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = After their previous encounter with multiple MegaBj\u00f6gens, the Healing Animals decide to put the Precure through a boot camp to improve on their teamwork. The group go to a quarry and practice working together but things don't seem to go very well, yet the girl manage to have fun regardless. Suddenly a MegaBj\u00f6gen appears along with a new Bj\u00f6gen General named Batetemoda. The girls transform and attempt to fight the MegaBj\u00f6gen only for Batetemoda to beat them back. However, the Precure manage to work as a team and defeat both Batetemoda and the MegaBj\u00f6gen and purify the Gem Spirit. Before disappearing, Batetemoda reveals he was created from the MegaBj\u00f6gen created by Daruizen, and that more will come. Nodoka and Chiyu agree that they will continue to work hard to prevent more Generals from being created, but Hinata secretly begins to have doubts. \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| Title               = To Quit Or To Not Quit? A Confused Hinata!\n| TranslitTitle       = Yameru? Yamenai? Mayoeru Hinata!\n| NativeTitle         = \u8f9e\u3081\u308b\uff1f\u8f9e\u3081\u306a\u3044\uff1f\u8ff7\u3048\u308b\u3072\u306a\u305f\uff01\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start dat